tr><td><strong>Severe</strong></td><td>Persistent symptoms for â‰¥6 hrs with â‰¥5 episodes of vomiting or retching/day</td><td>Significant: requires hospitalization for IV hydration</td></tr></tbody></table>'),(437,300,'section_two_label','Mtg'),(438,300,'sectiontwo','<h3>Management</h3><p>If NVP is impacting the patientâ€™s activities, some form of management should be initiated to prevent progression to HG.</p><ul><li>Administer medications on a scheduled basis with doses titrated to individual patient needs.</li><li>Patients with severe NVP or HG require urgent medical care due to dehydration and malnutrition.</li><li>After all other therapies have been considered and tried, enteral tube feeding and can be used in severe forms of HG.</li><li>Total Parental Nutrition (TPN) is not recommended.</li><li>A commercially fixed dose combination of doxylamine (antihistamine) and pyridoxine hydrochloride (Vitamin B6) is available for the treatment of nausea and vomiting of pregnancy. While the dosage is lower than non-fixed regimens, it may be more convenient for patient use. Medicaid preauthorization is required.</li></ul>'),(439,300,'section_three_label','Rx'),(440,300,'sectionthree','<div class=\"container-fluid\"><div class=\"accordion\" id=\"accordionNV2\"><div class=\"accordion-group\"><div class=\"accordion-heading\"><a class=\"accordion-toggle\" href=\"#collapseNVOne\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordionNV2\">Start with: <i class=\"icon-chevron-right pull-right\"></i></a></div><div class=\"accordion-body collapse\" id=\"collapseNVOne\" style=\"height: 0px;\"><div class=\"accordion-inner\"><!--  NV1 - Start with:   --><dl><dt>Drug</dt><dd>Vitamin B6</dd><dt>Dosage</dt><dd>25-50mg 3-4 time/day</dd><dt>Route</dt><dd>Oral</dd></dl></div></div></div><div class=\"accordion-group\"><div class=\"accordion-heading\"><a class=\"accordion-toggle\" href=\"#collapseNVTwo\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordionNV2\"> If no improvement add: <i class=\"icon-chevron-right pull-right\"></i></a></div><div class=\"accordion-body collapse\" id=\"collapseNVTwo\"><div class=\"accordion-inner\"><!--     NV2 - If no improvement add:  ---><dl><dt>Drug</dt><dd>Doxylamine (Unisom)</dd><dt>Dosage</dt><dd>12.6mg 3-4 time/day</dd><dt>Route</dt><dd>Oral or Rectal</dd></dl></div></div></div><div class=\"accordion-group\"><div class=\"accordion-heading\"><a class=\"accordion-toggle\" href=\"#collapseNVThree\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordionNV2\">If no improvement add:<i class=\"icon-chevron-right pull-right\"></i></a></div><div class=\"accordion-body collapse\" id=\"collapseNVThree\"><div class=\"accordion-inner\"><p><!--   NV3- If no improvement add:  ---></p><dl><dt>Drug</dt><dd>Promethazine (Phenergan)</dd><dt>Dosage</dt><dd>12.5-25mg every 4 hours</dd><dt>Route</dt><dd>Oral or Rectal</dd><dd>Â </dd><dt>OR</dt><dd>Â </dd><dt>Drug</dt><dd>Dimenhydrinate (Dramamine*)</dd><dt>Dosage</dt><dd>50-100mg every 4-6 hours</dd><dt>Route</dt><dd>Oral or Rectal</dd></dl></div></div></div><div class=\"accordion-group\"><div class=\"accordion-heading\"><a class=\"accordion-toggle\" href=\"#collapseNVFour\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordionNV2\">If no improvement and no dehydration add:<i class=\"icon-chevron-right pull-right\"></i></a></div><div class=\"accordion-body collapse\" id=\"collapseNVFour\"><div class=\"accordion-inner\"><p><!--   NV4- If no improvement and no dehydration add:  ---></p><dl><dt>Drug</dt><dd>Metoclopramide (Reglan)</dd><dt>Dosage</dt><dd>5-10mg every 8 hours</dd><dt>Route</dt><dd>IM or Oral</dd><dd>Â </dd><dt>OR</dt><dd>Â </dd><dt>Drug</dt><dd>Promethazine (Phenergan)</dd><dt>Dosage</dt><dd>12.5-25mg every 4 hours</dd><dt>Route</dt><dd>IM, Oral or Rectal</dd><dd>Â </dd><dt>OR</dt><dd>Â </dd><dt>Drug</dt><dd>Trimethobenzamide (Tebamide or Tigan)</dd><dt>Dosage</dt><dd>200mg every 6-8 hours</dd><dt>Route</dt><dd>Rectal</dd></dl></div></div></div><div class=\"accordion-group\"><div class=\"accordion-heading\"><a class=\"accordion-toggle\" href=\"#collapseNVFive\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordionNV2\">If no improvement and dehydration add:<i class=\"icon-chevron-right pull-right\"></i></a></div><div class=\"accordion-body collapse\" id=\"collapseNVFive\"><div class=\"accordion-inner\"><p><!--   NV5- If no improvement and dehydration add:  ---></p><dl><dt>Drug</dt><dd>IV fluids</dd><dt>Dosage</dt><dd>0.9% Saline <strong>OR</strong> 5% dextrose -0.9% saline</dd><dt>Route</dt><dd>IV</dd><dd>Â </dd><dt>AND</dt><dd>Â </dd><dt>Drug</dt><dd>Dimenhydrinate (Dramamine*)</dd><dt>Dosage</dt><dd>50-100mg every 4-6 hours</dd><dt>Route</dt><dd>IV</dd><dd>Â </dd><dt>OR</dt><dd>Â </dd><dt>Drug</dt><dd>Promethazine (Phenergan)</dd><dt>Dosage</dt><dd>12.5-25mg every 4 hours</dd><dt>Route</dt><dd>IV</dd></dl></div></div></div><div class=\"accordion-group\"><div class=\"accordion-heading\"><a class=\"accordion-toggle\" href=\"#collapseNVSix\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordionNV2\">If no improvement and dehydration add:<i class=\"icon-chevron-right pull-right\"></i></a></div><div class=\"accordion-body collapse\" id=\"collapseNVSix\"><div class=\"accordion-inner\"><p><!--   NV6- If no improvement add:  ---></p><dl><dt>Drug</dt><dd>Ondansetron (Zofran)</dd><dt>Dosage</dt><dd>8mg IV over 15 minutes every 12 hrs</dd><dt>Route</dt><dd>IV</dd></dl></div></div></div><div class=\"accordion-group\"><div class=\"accordion-heading\"><a class=\"accordion-toggle\" href=\"#collapseNVSeven\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordionNV2\">If still no improvement:<i class=\"icon-chevron-right pull-right\"></i></a></div><div class=\"accordion-body collapse\" id=\"collapseNVSeven\"><div class=\"accordion-inner\"><p><!--   NV7- If still no improvement:  ---></p><dl><dt>Drug</dt><dd>Consult with MFM and consider transfer</dd><dt>Â </dt><dd>Â </dd><dt>Â </dt><dd>Â </dd></dl></div></div></div></div><p><!-- end of accordion --></p><p><!-- end of container-fluid  --></p></div>'),(441,300,'section_four_label',''),(442,300,'sectionfour',''),(443,300,'section_five_label',''),(444,300,'sectionfive',''),(445,300,'version','5/13/2013'),(356,229,'section_one_label','Mtg'),(357,229,'sectionone','<h3>GBS OB Management</h3><ul><li>ACOG and CDC recommend universal screening of all pregnant women by vaginal and rectal culture at 35-37 weeks gestation unless the patient has had GBS bacteruria this pregnancy or a previous infant affected by early onset GBS disease.</li><li>If a cunture has not been performed or results are not avaiable, pregnanct women should receive antiobiotics based on the following risk factors:</li></ul><blockquote><ul style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><li>Threatened preterm, labor (&lt; 37 weeks GA)</li></ul></blockquote><blockquote><ul style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><li>Intrapartum fever (&gt;100 F)</li></ul></blockquote><blockquote><ul style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><li>Rupture of membranes &gt; 18 hours</li></ul></blockquote><ul><li>All women who have had a child affected by early-onset GBS disease should receive intrapartum prophylaxis and no culture is needed.</li><li>For women who were colonized in a prior pregnancy but did NOT have a child affected by GBS, she may not remain colonized and therefore a culture should be performed.</li><li>A positive urine culture for GBS during the current pregnancy mandates intrapartum antibiotic prophylaxis irrespective of the vagino-rectal culture result and thus, in such women, the 35-37 week culture is not needed.</li><li>GBS prophylaxis is not needed in women who undergo <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>pre-labor, pre-membrane rupture</strong></span><strong> </strong>cesarean delivery. Women planning repeat cesarean delivery should still undergo screening for GBS as rupture of membranes may occur prior to the scheduled cesarean.</li></ul>'),(358,229,'section_two_label','Rx'),(359,229,'sectiontwo','<p>Patient allergic to penicillin?</p><ul class=\"nav nav-pills\"><li><a href=\"#q1yes\" data-toggle=\"tab\">Yes</a></li><li><a href=\"#q1no\" data-toggle=\"tab\">No</a></li></ul><div class=\"tab-content\"><!-- beginning of q1 container  --><div class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"q1yes\"><p>Patient with history of any of the following after receiving penicillin or cephalosporin?</p><ul><li>Anaphylaxis</li><li>Angioedema</li><li>Respiratory distress</li><li>Urticaria</li></ul><ul class=\"nav nav-pills\"><li><a href=\"#q2yes\" data-toggle=\"tab\">Yes</a></li><li><a href=\"#q2no\" data-toggle=\"tab\">No</a></li></ul><div class=\"tab-content\"><!-- beginning of q2 container --><div class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"q2yes\"><p>Isolate sensitive to clindamycin <strong>AND</strong> erythromycin*</p><p>*Susceptibility testing must be performed to both (despite the fact that erythromycin is not an appropriate antibiotic) because some isolates with erythromycin resistance will also be partly resistant to clindamycin despite the results of susceptibility testing.</p><ul class=\"nav nav-pills\"><li><a href=\"#q3yes\" data-toggle=\"tab\">Yes</a></li><li><a href=\"#q3no\" data-toggle=\"tab\">No</a></li></ul><div class=\"tab-content\"><!-- beginning of q3 container  --><div class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"q3yes\"><p>Clindamycin, 900 mg IV every 8 hours until delivery</p></div><div class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"q3no\">Vancomycin, 1 gram IV every 12 hours until delivery</div></div><p><!-- end of q3 container  --></p></div><div class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"q2no\">Cefazolin, 2 grams IV initial dose, then 1 gram every 8 hours until delivery</div></div><p><!-- end of q2 container  --></p></div><div class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"q1no\">Penicillin G. 5 million units IV, then 2.5-3.0 million units IV every 4 hours until delivery or Ampicillin, 2 grams IV initial dose, then 1 gram IV every 4 hours or 2 grams every 6 hours until delivery</div></div><p><!-- end of q1 container --></p>'),(360,229,'section_three_label',''),(361,229,'sectionthree',''),(362,229,'section_four_label',''),(363,229,'sectionfour',''),(364,229,'section_five_label',''),(365,229,'sectionfive',''),(446,304,'_wp_attached_file','2013/07/install-APEC-App.pdf'),(642,733,'_edit_last','3'),(641,418,'description',''),(453,308,'_wp_attached_file','2013/07/APEC_install_img001.jpeg'),(454,308,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:368;s:6:\"height\";i:716;s:4:\"file\";s:32:\"2013/07/APEC_install_img001.jpeg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:8:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:32:\"APEC_install_img001-150x150.jpeg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:6:\"medium\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:32:\"APEC_install_img001-154x300.jpeg\";s:5:\"width\";i:154;s:6:\"height\";i:300;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:13:\"wpbs-featured\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:32:\"APEC_install_img001-368x300.jpeg\";s:5:\"width\";i:368;s:6:\"height\";i:300;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:18:\"wpbs-featured-home\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:32:\"APEC_install_img001-368x311.jpeg\";s:5:\"width\";i:368;s:6:\"height\";i:311;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:22:\"wpbs-featured-carousel\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:32:\"APEC_install_img001-368x400.jpeg\";s:5:\"width\";i:368;s:6:\"height\";i:400;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:15:\"bones-thumb-600\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:31:\"APEC_install_img001-77x150.jpeg\";s:5:\"width\";i:77;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:15:\"bones-thumb-300\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:32:\"APEC_install_img001-300x100.jpeg\";s:5:\"width\";i:300;s:6:\"height\";i:100;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:14:\"post-thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:32:\"APEC_install_img001-125x125.jpeg\";s:5:\"width\";i:125;s:6:\"height\";i:125;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:10:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\"